{% extends 'extractors/_meta/extractor.j2' %}

{% block instructions %}
You are the **classifier** for curator. Read the source. Produce
two pieces of metadata:

1. **Quintet** — five orthogonal slots driving Stage 2 extractor
   selection. Pick exactly one value per slot from the vocabulary
   block below.
2. **Topic** — a 3-12 word descriptor of the source's primary subject
   matter, used as a steering hint for downstream extractors.

## Quintet vocabulary

The full vocabulary lives at {{ vars.quintet_path }}. The relevant
section (slots + per-value descriptions) is included verbatim
below; consult it to pick each slot's value.

```yaml
{% include 'curator/quintet.yaml' %}
```

## Rules

- Pick exactly one value per slot. No multi-valued slots.
- The source content is your only ground truth. Never invoke model
  priors or external knowledge about the topic.
- When a slot is ambiguous, pick the more conservative value.
- Cite source evidence in `reasoning` (quote a phrase, mention a
  section heading, etc.).
{% endblock %}

{% block builder_calls %}

    curator.sh builders add {{ task.output_path }} \
        --set quintet.media=<media> \
        --set quintet.form=<form> \
        --set quintet.register=<register> \
        --set quintet.discipline=<discipline> \
        --set quintet.audience=<audience> \
        --set topic='<3-12 word descriptor>' \
        --set reasoning='<2-4 sentences citing source evidence>'

All seven fields are required.
{% endblock %}
